<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="254" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1616,2039]" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1616,1642]" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Type data:</emphasis>
This variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1876" box="[463,640,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis box="[463,640,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Centris muralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed from male and female specimens collected by the Danish hymenopterist Anders Christian Jensen-Haarup (1863–1934) in 
<collectingRegion box="[920,1027,1652,1678]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
, northwest 
<collectingCountry box="[1158,1273,1652,1678]" name="Argentina" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. During 1904, Jensen-Haarup made a collecting trip to 
<collectingRegion box="[622,729,1688,1714]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
, returning to 
<collectingCountry box="[888,992,1688,1714]" name="Denmark" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Denmark</collectingCountry>
the next year. In 1906, he returned to 
<collectingRegion box="[151,258,1724,1750]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
, this time accompanied by the Danish entomologist Peter Jörgensen (1870–1937). According to the information of the label of the 
<typeStatus box="[438,525,1761,1787]" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">syntype</typeStatus>
male found at 
<collectionCode box="[691,754,1761,1787]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="23" pageNumber="254" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
, that specimen ‒here designated the lectotype‒ was collected during his second trip. The specimen has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[919,1030,1796,1822]" name="Argentina" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Argentina</collectingCountry>
<collectingRegion box="[1040,1144,1796,1822]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
[printed] 3.11 [handwritten] 190 [printed] 6 [handwritten] Jensen [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Fr." authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1908" box="[740,1056,1832,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="muralis" variety="melanopus">
<emphasis box="[740,759,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[774,860,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">muralis</emphasis>
v. 
<emphasis box="[895,1016,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="254">melanopus</emphasis>
Fr.
</taxonomicName>
